                <head>96. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The Ministerial Council of the Organization for Economic Cooperation and
                    Development met in Paris December 2–3, 1964. Under Secretary of State <persName
                        corresp="#p_BGW1">George W. Ball</persName> headed the U.S. Delegation. A
                    summary of the <gloss target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss> Ministerial proceedings is
                    in two parts, <gloss target="#t_Cedto1">CEDTO</gloss> A–386 from Paris, December
                    11, and <gloss target="#t_Cedto1">CEDTO</gloss> A–392 from Paris, December 11,
                    both in Department of State, Central Files, ECIN 3 <gloss target="#t_OECD1"
                        >OECD</gloss>. For text of the December 3 communiqué, <hi rend="italic">see
                        American Foreign Policy: Current Documents</hi>, 1964, pages 497–499.</p>
                <p>Background and talking points papers on U.S. preparations for and participation
                    in the <gloss target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss> Ministerial Council meeting are in
                    the Washington National Records Center, RG 286, <gloss target="#t_DAC1"
                        >DAC</gloss> Material: FRC 70 <gloss target="#t_A1">A</gloss> 5922,
                        Meetings—<gloss target="#t_OECD1">OECD</gloss> Ministerial Dec. 2–3, 1964,
                    and Department of State, Conference Files: Lot 66 <gloss target="#t_D1"
                        >D</gloss> 110, CF 2456–2457.</p>
            </div>
